taxize

Source: https://github.com/ropensci/taxize
CRAN: https://cran.rstudio.com/web/packages/taxize/

taxize - two organizing principles

  • Data sources
    • Lots of data sources, currently 20
  • Verbs (ish)
    • classification()
    • children()
    • downstream()
    • upstream()
    • comm2sci() / sci2comm()
    • resolve()
    • synonyms()
    • lowest_common

Why taxize?

A single easy to use user interface to many data sources can simplify science, and make it more reproducible

Other taxonomic tools

  • taxa - taxonomic classes - in development https://github.com/ropenscilabs/taxa
  • binomen - manipulations on taxonomic classes - https://github.com/ropenscilabs/binomen
  • taxizedb - taxonomic databases - https://github.com/ropenscilabs/taxizedb

others

  • Taxonstand - https://cran.rstudio.com/web/packages/Taxonstand/
